  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Circular Economy in Ghana: towards an EPR system for plastics</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at the development of an Extended Producer Responsibility organisation for plastics in Ghana. In close cooperation with GIZ a series of hands on webinars will be set up. Furthermore, a mini-pilot will be launched to test the future EPR set up in real. This mini-pilot will be aligned with the SBIR Plastic Whale pilot project (aiming at collecting, processing and producing plastics products including the informal sector).This project is part of a strategy and a series of aid and trade projects of the EKN in Accra to support  both the introduction of best fitting solutions private sector development for waste management and circular economy. And explore business opportunities for the Dutch sector.</narrative>
  </description>
